    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="710" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Missionaries at all interior posts reported safe and protected by
                            soldiers. Bloody outbreak Ourfa 28th. Safe-conduct promised for Miss
                            Shattuck, who is there alone, to Aintab. Porte agrees that relief for
                            destitute at Harpoot may be extended under a commission of three—Barnum,
                            one Turk, one native Christian. He has American and English charity
                            funds. The Porte denies complicity of officers or soldiers in destroying
                            American property. Am ready with data as to damages to demand indemnity.
                            Shall I do so now and consent to send a commission to inquire if
                            requested, or wait for further instructions?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
